title: Greenland may have been green and ice-free 416,000 years ago
description: Greenland may have been green and ice-free as recently as 416,000 years ago, new research has found.

title: A big cat is on the loose in Berlin - and the locals fear their pet dogs are 'ideal lion food'
description: On the outskirts of Berlin, an uninvited summer visitor has been spotted.

title: How killer whale mothers keep their calves out of fights
description: Mums will do anything to support their children - and when it comes to orcas, it even extends to fending off bullies.

title: Shakira faces new investigation over alleged tax fraud in Spain
description: Colombian singer Shakira faces more trouble from Spain's tax office after a court agreed to open an investigation into two more possible cases of  tax fraud.

title: Ronan Keating sings tribute to brother at his funeral mass
description: Ronan Keating has performed a musical tribute to his brother Ciaran Keating at his funeral mass in Ireland.

title: Movement of British diplomats in Russia restricted by Moscow
description: Russia has restricted the movement of British diplomats within the country in a response to "hostile actions" from London, the Russian Foreign Ministry has said.

title: 'Regrettable choice of words': EU backs down after calling Falklands by Argentine name - PM
description: Rishi Sunak has criticised the EU for a "regrettable choice of words" after it appeared to endorse the Argentine name for the Falkland Islands.

title: Friend of OceanGate CEO says he created a 'mousetrap for billionaires'
description: A friend of late OceanGate CEO Stockton Rush - who died in the Titan submersible when it imploded near the wreck of the Titanic last month - has claimed he knew the expeditions would end in disaster but continued to design a "mousetrap for billionaires".

title: Women's World Cup kicks off with wins for co-hosts - as security increased after shooting
description: New Zealand has kicked off the Women's World Cup by beating Norway in a match played in front of beefed-up security following a shooting incident that left three people dead.

title: Gang rape investigated as abducted Indian women paraded naked in video
description: There is outrage in India over a video of tribal women being paraded naked and assaulted - with one allegedly gang raped during the incident in the northeastern state of Manipur.

title: Six dead as Balkans hit by powerful storm
description: Six people have died in a powerful storm which has battered much of the Balkans - while Southern Europe continues to face a searing heatwave.

title: Trains to Europe may be better for the climate, but they're four times more expensive than flying
description: Taking the train to holiday spots in Europe is four times more expensive than flying on average, according to new research.

title: North Korea 'not responding' to US over soldier who crossed border
description: US officials have attempted to contact North Korean counterparts over an American soldier who bolted across the border from South Korea - but say they are yet to hear back from Pyongyang.

title: Rare deep sea oarfish known as 'harbinger of doom' spotted off Taiwan coast
description: Divers off the northeast coast of Taiwan have filmed a rare encounter with a giant oarfish with large holes in its body.

title: Lucky Powerball player scoops $1bn jackpot
description: A Powerball player has scooped a $1.08bn jackpot (£835bn) - with the life-changing amount the third-biggest prize in the lottery's history.

title: Suspected lioness on the loose on the outskirts of Berlin
description: A wild animal - believed to be a lioness - is on the loose on the outskirts of German capital Berlin.

title: Swedish embassy in Baghdad stormed by protesters over planned Koran burning
description: Protesters angered by the planned burning of a copy of the Koran in Stockholm have stormed the Swedish embassy in Baghdad and lit a fire.

title: Dingo euthanised after jogger mauled on beach
description: The leader of a pack of dingoes that mauled a jogger on a beach in Australia has been put down.
